LibAmpl
=======

LibAmpl is a simple set of files used to build a shared library
from the AMPL Library source files. This shared library can then
be used with a variety of software. Current software projects
using LibAmpl include

 o   nlpy     http://nlpy.sf.net
 o   DrAmpl   http://www.gerad.ca/~orban/drampl
 o   MiniAmpl http://github.com/dpo/miniampl

To report problems with LibAmpl please e-mail dominique.orban@gerad.ca

See the INSTALL file for installation directions.

If you are running OSX, make sure you read Readme.macosx!

Enjoy!
Dominique Orban
dominique.orban@gerad.ca
Montreal, January 2007
